The DC bus voltage of the system under abrupt load variations is shown in Fig. 18. Even though the three controllers show a good performance, it should be noted that the PID controllers are slower than both FOSM and SOSM. Particularly, FOSM exhibits the fastest recovery time, but with the highest under/overshoot (see left zoomed area) and high chattering. On the other hand, SOSM shows and intermediate recovery time, less under/overshoot and neglectable chattering. It is important to notice also that while the FC current is slowly changing (see right zoomed area), the PID controllers are not able to accurately regulate the DC bus voltage.Fig. 18
